[1] Congo DR (Katanga)
Date: 8 May 2015
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans. edited]
http://radiookapi.net


About 100 children from 0-5 years of age have died since January 2015 as a result of the measles epidemic in the territory of Pweto (Katanga), said the head of Moero sector, Shadrach Kazembe, on 7 May 2015. He attributed the rise of the epidemic to the movement of people due to repeated incursions of the Mayi-Mayi in the area, located more than 200 km away from Lubumbashi, the capital of Katanga.

"It's been several years since this disease was not registered in our health area. With the movement caused by [Mayi-Mayi], there was spread of this disease," said Shadrach Kazembe.

Cases of deaths have been recorded in the health areas of Dikulushi and Mubanga Katendeji.

Kazembe said that possible solutions are being considered by the NGO Alima, who has run a vaccination program in the country against measles since 13 May 2015. Acknowledging the epidemic in the region, the chief doctor of Kilwa health zone reported 40 fatal cases.

--
